### 2018

* __Matheson, GJ__ (2018). We need to talk about reliability: Making better use of test retest studies for study design and interpretation. *bioRxiv, 274894.*

* __Matheson, GJ__, Plavén-Sigray, P, Louzolo, Anaïs, Borg, J, Farde, L, Petrovic, P & Cervenka, S (2018). Dopamine D1 receptor availability is not associated with delusional ideation measures of psychosis proneness. *bioRxiv, 321646.*

* Plavén-Sigray, P, __Matheson, GJ__, Gustavsson, Petter, Stenkrona, P, Halldin, C, Farde, L & Cervenka, S (2018). Is dopamine D1 receptor availability related to social behavior? A positron emission tomography replication study. *PloS one, 13, e0193770.*

* Plavén-Sigray, P, __Matheson, GJ__, Cselényi, Z, Jucaite, A, Farde, L & Cervenka, S (2018). Test-retest reliability and convergent validity of \(R)-[11C] PK11195 outcome measures without arterial input function. *bioRxiv, 298992.*

* Plavén-Sigray, P, __Matheson, GJ__, Collste, K, Ashok, AH, Coughlin, JM, Howes, OD, Mizrahi, R, Pomper, MG, Rusjan, P, Veronese, M & others (2018). Positron Emission Tomography Studies of the Glial Cell Marker Translocator Protein in Patients With Psychosis: A Meta-analysis Using Individual Participant Data. *Biological psychiatry*




### 2017

* __Matheson, GJ__, Stenkrona, P, Cselényi, Z, Plavén-Sigray, P, Halldin, C, Farde, L & Cervenka, S (2017). Reliability of volumetric and surface-based normalisation and smoothing techniques for PET analysis of the cortex: A test-retest analysis using [11 C] SCH-23390. *NeuroImage, 155, 344-353.*

* __Matheson, GJ__, Plavén-Sigray, P, Forsberg, A, Varrone, A, Farde, L & Cervenka, S (2017). Assessment of simplified ratio-based approaches for quantification of PET [11 C] PBR28 data. *EJNMMI research, 7, 58.*

* Plavén-Sigray, P\*, __Matheson, GJ\*__, Schiffler, BC\* & Thompson, WH (2017). The readability of scientific texts is decreasing over time. *eLife, 6.*

* Plavén-Sigray, P, Hedman, E, Victorsson, P, __Matheson, GJ__, Forsberg, A, Djurfeldt, Diana R, Rück, C, Halldin, C, Lindefors, N & Cervenka, S (2017). Extrastriatal dopamine D2-receptor availability in social anxiety disorder. *European Neuropsychopharmacology, 27, 462-469.*

* Griffioen, G, __Matheson, GJ__, Cervenka, S, Farde, L & Borg, J (2017). Serotonin 5-HT1A receptor binding and self-transcendence in healthy control subjects-a replication study using Bayesian hypothesis testing. *bioRxiv, 226092.*


